The paper deals with the problem of single image super-resolution, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves collaborative filtering and iterative back-projection, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of self-similarity, which is a concept that has been explored in both machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, it is likely that the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.AI (artificial intelligence).
